caption: get over the fear  how to do your first handstand hold the wall facing handstand is basically an advanced plank  it doe emphasize shoulder stability more than the standard plank  these are the benefit of handstand  even if you have a desk job  ‚Ä¢ they train your core and glute to support a healthy back  ‚Ä¢ they help you maintain good posture  to do a handstand  you need adequate overhead mobility and thoracic mobility  which we dont tend to challenge enough in our day to day activity  use it or lose it    ‚Ä¢ they strengthen the muscle that help improve posture and keep your shoulder pain free  such a the rotator cuff  serratus anterior  and lower trapezius  step  <Number>  keep your ab tight a you walk your hand and foot up into the handstand position  <Number>  a you hold  push the floor away from to keep your shoulder muscle active  <Number>  ensure good core stability by keeping your rib pulled towards your spine  in other word  maintain a good hollow body position  the muscle of the butt and front of the thigh should also be tense  not just the upper body and core  <Number>  while the goal is to bring your hand a close to the wall a you can  start in a more horizontal position if needed and gradually work towards a more vertical position a you improve strength and stability  whatever position you choose  always push the floor away and keep your rib pulled towards your spine  if you give this a try  leave a comment on how this go for you  #stem #science #technology #engineer #medicine #scientist #research #academic #homeworkout #vancouver #yvr #personaltrainer #kinesiology posture
